":"You can use "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"onChange"},{"text":" to trigger a side effect as the result of a","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"value changing, such as an "},{"code":"Environment","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" key or a "},{"code":"Binding","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":"."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The system may call the action closure on the main actor, so avoid"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"long-running tasks in the closure. If you need to perform such tasks,"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"detach an asynchronous background task."}]},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"When the value changes, the new version of the closure will be called,"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"so any captured values will have their values from the time that the"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"observed value has its new value. The old and new observed values are"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"passed into the closure. In the following code example, ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"PlayerView"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"passes both the old and new values to the model.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"codeListing","code":["struct PlayerView: View {","    var episode: Episode","    @State private var playState: PlayState = .paused","","    var body: some View {","        VStack {","            Text(episode.title)","            Text(episode.showTitle)","            PlayButton(playState: $playState)","        }","        .onChange(of: playState) { oldState, newState in","            model.playStateDidChange(from: oldState, to: newState)","        }","    }","}"],"syntax":null}]}],"variants":[{"paths":["\/documentation\/markdownview\/swiftuicore\/view\/onchange(of:initial:_:)-1f9lu"],"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}]}],"identifier":{"interfaceLanguage